                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13815479" author="rohini" created="Thu, 7 Nov 2013 00:15:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can just run pig  -Dmapreduce.job.cache.archives=&quot;hdfs path for the tgz file#symlink&quot; or do the same inside the script with set command. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13815751" author="jdonofrio" created="Thu, 7 Nov 2013 08:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That works but it is not a very clean solution. UDF&apos;s should be able to add archives to the distributed cache as they do currently with files. Your solution forces users of a UDF&apos;s to have to know to add the archive explicitly to use the UDF instead of letting the UDF handle it for them&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13817087" author="jdonofrio" created="Fri, 8 Nov 2013 07:32:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch that adds files ending with .zip, .tgz, .tar.gz, or .tar as DistributedCache archives instead of files&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13818383" author="cheolsoo" created="Sun, 10 Nov 2013 07:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks reasonable to me. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;Rohini Palaniswamy&lt;/a&gt;, do you have objections with Jim&apos;s patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819504" author="rohini" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 22:21:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am good. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jdonofrio&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jdonofrio&quot;&gt;Jim Donofrio&lt;/a&gt;, do you want to update the pattern to check for symlinks as well or this is sufficient to support your usecase? Currently it only looks for files ending with .tar, .zip, etc. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819520" author="jdonofrio" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 22:34:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is sufficient for now&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819679" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 12 Nov 2013 00:55:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thank you Jim!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
